        <div class="formCard" id="overview"
         style="border-color: rgba(59,130,246,.40); background: rgba(59,130,246,.05); scroll-margin-top: 20px;">
        <h2 style="margin-top: 0;">🚀 What Can This App Do?</h2>
        <div style="color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.8;">
            <p>
                <strong>Filament Tracker v2.0</strong> is a comprehensive inventory management system for 3D printing
                enthusiasts.
                Here's what makes it powerful:
            </p>

            <h3>📊 Core Features:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Multi-Spool Tracking</strong> - Track multiple spools of the same filament color. If you
                    have 3 spools of "Matte Black PLA", they're grouped together automatically
                </li>
                <li><strong>Smart Status Warnings</strong> - Visual indicators (green/yellow/red) show stock levels at a
                    glance with customizable thresholds
                </li>
                <li><strong>Usage Recording</strong> - Track how much filament you use per print or over time</li>
                <li><strong>Reusable Spool Management</strong> - Automatic tracking of reusable spools (Bambu Lab,
                    third-party) as they empty and become available for refills
                </li>
                <li><strong>Brand Management</strong> - Organized dropdown with your filament brands, easily add custom
                    brands on-the-fly
                </li>
            </ul>

            <h3>🎨 Organization Tools:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Advanced Search & Filtering</strong> - Find filaments by brand, color, type, finish, or
                    filter by stock level
                </li>
                <li><strong>Multiple Sort Options</strong> - Sort by date, weight, name, or color brightness (darkest to
                    lightest)
                </li>
                <li><strong>Color Brightness Sorting</strong> - Intelligently sorts filaments by how dark/light they
                    appear
                </li>
                <li><strong>Type Filtering</strong> - Quickly view only PLA, PETG, ASA, ABS, TPU, or NYLON filaments
                </li>
            </ul>

            <h3>⚙️ Customization & Data:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Configurable Thresholds</strong> - Set your own Low and Critical warning levels based on
                    your printing habits
                </li>
                <li><strong>Dark/Light Themes</strong> - Choose your preferred visual theme</li>
                <li><strong>CSV Import/Export</strong> - Backup your data or migrate from other systems</li>
                <li><strong>Offline & Private</strong> - All data stored locally on your computer, no cloud sync
                    required
                </li>
            </ul>

            <h3>💪 Advanced Capabilities:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Bulk Operations</strong> - Add multiple spools at once with the Quantity field</li>
                <li><strong>Detailed Record Keeping</strong> - Track storage location, purchase dates, notes, and more
                </li>
                <li><strong>Automatic Grouping</strong> - Spools with matching properties automatically group together
                </li>
                <li><strong>Real-Time Updates</strong> - Changes reflect immediately across the entire app</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>🧮 Print Cost Calculator:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Professional Cost Estimation</strong> - Calculate accurate 3D print costs including
                    materials, labor, machine costs, and more
                </li>
                <li><strong>Bambu Lab Printer Profiles</strong> - Pre-configured settings for popular Bambu Lab printers
                    (X1C, P1S, A1, H2 series)
                </li>
                <li><strong>Multi-Material Support</strong> - Track costs for prints using multiple filament types</li>
                <li><strong>PDF Export</strong> - Generate professional quotes for clients with detailed cost breakdowns
                </li>
            </ul>

            <h3>🖨️ Multi-Printer BambuLab Integration (NEW v2.0):</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>✨ Multiple Printer Support</strong> - Connect to multiple BambuLab printers simultaneously!
                </li>
                <li><strong>Real-Time Print Monitoring</strong> - Live progress, layer count, time remaining via direct
                    MQTT connection for all printers
                </li>
                <li><strong>Per-Printer Management</strong> - Independent connection control, settings, and status
                    tracking
                </li>
                <li><strong>AMS Slot Tracking</strong> - See all AMS slots with color, filament type, and sub-brand at a
                    glance (per printer)
                </li>
                <li><strong>MQTT Message Log</strong> - Filter by specific printer or view all printers' messages
                </li>
                <li><strong>MQTT Relay Server</strong> - Broadcast messages from multiple printers to external devices
                    (ESP32, Home Assistant)
                </li>
                <li><strong>Inventory Linking</strong> - Match AMS slots to your tracked inventory filaments</li>
                <li><strong>AMS Auto-Weight Sync</strong> - Automatically update spool weights from AMS RFID data (per
                    printer)
                </li>
            </ul>

            <p style="margin-top: 16px;">
                <em>💡 New to the app? Start by reading the "Adding New Filaments" section below, then explore the other
                    features!</em>
            </p>
        </div>
        @backToTop
    </div>

    <div class="formCard" id="inventory" style="scroll-margin-top: 20px;">
        <h2 style="margin-top: 0;">📦 Inventory Overview</h2>
        <div style="color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.8;">
            <p>
                The <strong>Inventory</strong> page is your main dashboard for tracking all your 3D printer filaments.
                Here's what you can do:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>View all filaments</strong> - Each card represents a unique filament (brand, type, color
                    combination)
                </li>
                <li><strong>Multiple spools</strong> - If you have multiple spools of the same filament, they're grouped
                    together with a "×N" badge
                </li>
                <li><strong>Status indicators</strong>:
                    <ul>
                        <li><span style="color: var(--ok);">✓ Green (OK)</span> - Above your Low threshold (default:
                            500g)
                        </li>
                        <li><span style="color: var(--warn);">⚡ Yellow (Low)</span> - Below Low threshold but above
                            Critical threshold (default: 250g-500g)
                        </li>
                        <li><span style="color: var(--danger);">⚠️ Red (Critical)</span> - Below your Critical threshold
                            (default: 250g)
                        </li>
                        <li>💡 <em>You can customize these thresholds in Settings!</em></li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li><strong>Search & Filter</strong> - Use the search box to find filaments by brand, color, type, or
                    finish. Toggle "Low Only" to show just low and critical stock
                </li>
                <li><strong>Sort options</strong> - Multiple sorting choices:
                    <ul>
                        <li><em>Newest First</em> (default) - Most recently added filaments at the top</li>
                        <li><em>Oldest First</em> - Oldest filaments first (good for using FIFO)</li>
                        <li><em>Remaining ↓</em> - Highest remaining weight first</li>
                        <li><em>Remaining ↑</em> - Lowest remaining weight first (find what needs using)</li>
                        <li><em>Name A→Z</em> - Alphabetical by color name</li>
                        <li><em>Name Z→A</em> - Reverse alphabetical</li>
                        <li><em>🌑 Color (Dark→Light)</em> - Sort by color brightness, darkest colors first</li>
                        <li><em>☀️ Color (Light→Dark)</em> - Sort by color brightness, lightest colors first</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li><strong>Click any filament</strong> to open detailed view where you can:
                    <ul>
                        <li>See all spools for that filament</li>
                        <li>Record usage (subtract grams)</li>
                        <li>Edit spool details</li>
                        <li>Delete spools</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        @backToTop
    </div>

    <div class="formCard" id="adding" style="scroll-margin-top: 20px;">
        <h2 style="margin-top: 0;">➕ Adding New Filaments</h2>
        <div style="color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.8;">
            <p>
                Use the <strong>Add Filament</strong> page to add new filament spools to your inventory.
            </p>
            <h3>Required Fields:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Brand</strong> - Select from your saved brands or choose "➕ Other (Add Custom)" to add a new
                    brand
                    <ul>
                        <li>New brands are automatically saved and will appear in the dropdown for future use</li>
                        <li>Manage your brand list in the Settings page</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li><strong>Type</strong> - Material type (PLA, PETG, ASA, ABS, TPU, NYLON)</li>
                <li><strong>Color Name</strong> - Descriptive name for the color (e.g., "Jeans Blue", "Forest Green")
                </li>
                <li><strong>Color Code</strong> - Hex color code (e.g., #FF0000 for red) - shows a preview</li>
                <li><strong>Total Weight</strong> - Full weight of the spool in grams (typically 1000g)</li>
                <li><strong>Weight Remaining</strong> - Current weight remaining (start with full weight for new spools)
                </li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Optional Fields:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Finish/Variant</strong> - Special characteristics like Matte, Silk, Carbon Fiber, Wood, etc.
                </li>
                <li><strong>Quantity</strong> - Add multiple identical spools at once</li>
                <li><strong>Spool Type</strong>:
                    <ul>
                        <li><em>On Spool</em> - Filament comes on its own spool</li>
                        <li><em>Refill</em> - Refill filament without a spool (needs a reusable spool)</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li><strong>Spool Material</strong> - Plastic, Cardboard, or Reusable spool</li>
                <li><strong>Reusable Spool</strong> - Check if this spool can be reused after emptying</li>
                <li><strong>Diameter</strong> - Usually 1.75mm or 2.85mm</li>
                <li><strong>Storage Location</strong> - Where you keep this filament (e.g., "Shelf A", "Drawer 2")</li>
                <li><strong>Notes</strong> - Any additional information</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Example Scenarios:</h3>
            <p><strong>Scenario 1: Bambu Lab PLA Matte with 3 refills and 1 on reusable spool</strong></p>
            <ol>
                <li>Add the filament once with all details</li>
                <li>Set Quantity to 4 (3 refills + 1 spool)</li>
                <li>Later, you can manage each spool individually in the detail view</li>
            </ol>

            <p><strong>Scenario 2: Adding a refill to existing filament (Restocking)</strong></p>
            <ol>
                <li>Go to the Inventory page</li>
                <li>Click on the existing filament card</li>
                <li>In the detail modal, click the "➕ Add New Spool" button</li>
                <li>Fill in the spool details (type, weight, material)</li>
                <li>Click "Add Spool" to add it to the existing filament</li>
                <li>Your new spool will be grouped with the existing ones</li>
            </ol>

            <p>
                <em>Tip: When you restock a filament with the same brand, type, finish, and color,
                    always add it through the detail modal to keep everything grouped together. This way
                    you can track multiple spools of the same filament and see your total remaining stock.</em>
            </p>
        </div>
        @backToTop
    </div>

    <div class="formCard" id="spools" style="scroll-margin-top: 20px;">
        <h2 style="margin-top: 0;">🔁 Managing Reusable Spools</h2>
        <div style="color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.8;">
            <p>
                The <strong>Spools</strong> page helps you track your reusable spools separate from filaments.
            </p>
            <h3>What are Reusable Spools?</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Bambu Lab official reusable spools</li>
                <li>Third-party reusable spools</li>
                <li>Empty spools from previous filaments that can be refilled</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>How It Works (Automatic Tracking):</h3>
            <p>The app automatically tracks reusable spools for you:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>When you add a filament</strong> and check "Reusable Spool" → The app automatically marks a
                    spool as "In Use"
                </li>
                <li><strong>When you use up a filament</strong> (weight reaches 0g) → The app automatically marks the
                    spool as "Available"
                </li>
                <li><strong>When you import CSV</strong> with reusable spools → They're automatically added to your
                    spool inventory
                </li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Status Tracking:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Available</strong> - Empty spools ready to accept a refill</li>
                <li><strong>In Use</strong> - Currently has filament loaded (automatically set)</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Manual Management:</h3>
            <p>You can also manually add reusable spools to your inventory:</p>
            <ol>
                <li>Go to the <strong>Spools</strong> page</li>
                <li>Click "➕ Add Reusable Spool"</li>
                <li>Select the material type and quantity</li>
                <li>These will be marked as "Available" until you load filament on them</li>
            </ol>

            <p>
                <em>Tip: Keep track of your reusable spools so you know how many refills you can use before
                    needing to empty a spool or buy more reusable spools. The app handles the "In Use" status
                    automatically based on your filament inventory.</em>
            </p>
        </div>
        @backToTop
    </div>

    <div class="formCard" id="calculator" style="scroll-margin-top: 20px;">
        <h2 style="margin-top: 0;">🧮 Print Cost Calculator</h2>
        <div style="color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.8;">
            <p>
                The <strong>Calculator</strong> page helps you estimate costs for 3D printing projects and create
                professional quotes.
                Perfect for hobbyists pricing their prints or businesses quoting clients.
            </p>

            <h3>Key Features:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Comprehensive Cost Breakdown</strong> - Tracks materials, labor, machine depreciation,
                    electricity, hardware, and packaging
                </li>
                <li><strong>Printer Profiles</strong> - Pre-configured settings for Bambu Lab printers with accurate
                    depreciation and power consumption
                </li>
                <li><strong>Multi-Material Projects</strong> - Add multiple filaments with different colors and types
                </li>
                <li><strong>Inventory Integration</strong> - The filament dropdown shows <strong>Brand · Type ·
                        Sub-Brand · Color</strong> so you can identify exactly which spool you're costing
                </li>
                <li><strong>Pricing Presets</strong> - Quick pricing with margins: Competitive (25%), Standard (40%),
                    Premium (60%), Luxury (80%), or Custom
                </li>
                <li><strong>PDF Export</strong> - Generate professional quotes to share with clients</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Setting Up a Cost Estimate:</h3>
            <ol>
                <li><strong>Project Details</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Part Name</strong> - Name of the item you're printing</li>
                        <li><strong>Printer Profile</strong> - Select your Bambu printer to auto-fill settings</li>
                        <li><strong>Print Time</strong> - Hours and minutes from your slicer</li>
                        <li><strong>Handling Time</strong> - Time for post-processing, packaging, etc.</li>
                        <li><strong>Hardware Cost</strong> - Screws, inserts, or other components</li>
                        <li><strong>Packaging Cost</strong> - Boxes, bubble wrap, shipping materials</li>
                        <li><strong>VAT Rate</strong> - Tax percentage (default: 25% for Denmark)</li>
                        <li><strong>Batch Size</strong> - Number of parts in this run</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>

                <li><strong>Materials (Multi-Material)</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Inventory Integration:</strong> Select filaments directly from your inventory
                            <ul>
                                <li>Dropdown shows: <strong>"Brand · Type · Sub-Brand - Color Name"</strong> (e.g.,
                                    "Bambu Lab · PLA · Matte - Charcoal")
                                </li>
                                <li>Prices auto-fill from your purchase history (weighted average)</li>
                                <li>If no price is set, defaults to 149 per kg (editable)</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                        <li><strong>Manual Entry:</strong> Or enter custom material details
                            <ul>
                                <li>Select "Manual Entry" from dropdown</li>
                                <li>Enter any price per kilogram</li>
                                <li>Perfect for materials not in your inventory</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                        <li>Enter weight used in grams for each material</li>
                        <li>Click "+ Add Material" to add more materials for multi-color prints</li>
                        <li>Each material can be from inventory or manual entry</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>


                <li><strong>Advanced Settings</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Hourly Rate</strong> - Your labor cost per hour (default: 200 DKK/hr)</li>
                        <li><strong>Material Factor</strong> - Multiplier for waste/failed prints (default: 1.1 = 10%
                            extra)
                        </li>
                        <li><strong>Printer Price</strong> - Original cost of your printer</li>
                        <li><strong>Estimated Lifetime</strong> - Years you expect the printer to last</li>
                        <li><strong>Uptime Percent</strong> - How much of the time your printer is actively printing
                        </li>
                        <li><strong>Annual Maintenance</strong> - Yearly cost for replacement parts</li>
                        <li><strong>Power Consumption</strong> - Watts used during printing</li>
                        <li><strong>Electricity Price</strong> - Cost per kWh (default: 0.2 DKK/kWh)</li>
                        <li><strong>Buffer Factor</strong> - Safety margin multiplier (default: 1.3 = 30% buffer)</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ol>

            <h3>Understanding the Pricing:</h3>
            <p>The calculator shows several pricing options based on your unit cost:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Konkurrencedygtig (25% margin)</strong> - Competitive pricing for price-sensitive markets
                </li>
                <li><strong>Standard (40% margin)</strong> - Balanced pricing for most situations</li>
                <li><strong>Premium (60% margin)</strong> - Higher pricing for specialized or high-quality work</li>
                <li><strong>Luksus (80% margin)</strong> - Premium pricing for exclusive or custom pieces</li>
                <li><strong>Tilpasset</strong> - Custom margin using the slider (10-150%)</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Click any pricing row to select it. The selected price will be used in your PDF export.</p>

            <h3>Cost Breakdown:</h3>
            <p>View detailed per-unit costs for:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Material (filament cost with waste factor)</li>
                <li>Labor (handling time × hourly rate)</li>
                <li>Machine (depreciation + maintenance + electricity)</li>
                <li>Hardware (screws, inserts, etc.)</li>
                <li>Packaging (shipping materials)</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Exporting Quotes:</h3>
            <ol>
                <li>Configure all your project details</li>
                <li>Select your pricing option</li>
                <li>Click "Eksportér tilbud som PDF"</li>
                <li>A printable quote opens in a new window</li>
                <li>Use your browser's Print function to save as PDF</li>
            </ol>

            <h3>Printer Profile Benefits:</h3>
            <p>When you select a Bambu printer profile, the calculator automatically configures:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Accurate printer price for depreciation calculations</li>
                <li>Realistic lifetime expectations</li>
                <li>Typical uptime percentages</li>
                <li>Real-world maintenance costs</li>
                <li>Actual power consumption during printing</li>
                <li>Optimized material and buffer factors</li>
                <li>Print time multipliers for speed comparisons</li>
            </ul>

            <p>
                <em>💡 Pro Tips:</em>
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>Get print time and filament weight from your slicer for accurate estimates</li>
                <li>Include handling time for realistic labor costs</li>
                <li>Adjust the material factor based on your failure rate</li>
                <li>The buffer factor accounts for contingencies and business overhead</li>
                <li>Save quotes as PDFs to track pricing history</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        @backToTop
    </div>

    <div class="formCard" id="printer" style="scroll-margin-top: 20px;">
        <h2 style="margin-top: 0;">🖨️ Printer (Live Printers)</h2>
        <div style="color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.8;">
            <p>
                The <strong>Printer</strong> page shows real-time status cards for all enabled printers:
                online/offline state, printing progress, temperatures, and current job details.
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>Use the <strong>MQTT</strong> page to add/edit printers and connect/disconnect.</li>
                <li>Use the <strong>Printer</strong> page to monitor all configured printers in one view.</li>
                <li>Use the <strong>AMS</strong> page to link slots to inventory and verify spool matches.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                See <a href="#multiprinter">MQTT setup</a> for connection steps and
                <a href="#livetracker">Live Tracking Widget</a> for the compact top-bar status card.
            </p>
        </div>
        @backToTop
    </div>

    <div class="formCard" id="usage" style="scroll-margin-top: 20px;">
        <h2 style="margin-top: 0;">📊 Recording Usage</h2>
        <div style="color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.8;">
            <p>Track how much filament you've used with the improved usage recording system:</p>

            <h3>How to Record Usage:</h3>
            <ol>
                <li>Click on a filament card in the Inventory</li>
                <li>In the detail modal, select a specific spool from the list on the left</li>
                <li>In the <strong>"Manage Spool"</strong> section on the right:
                    <ul>
                        <li>Enter the amount used in grams</li>
                        <li>OR use quick buttons (-25g, -50g, -100g)</li>
                        <li>Click "Record" to subtract that amount</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li>Updates happen <strong>immediately</strong> - no need to close the modal!</li>
            </ol>

            <h3>Smart Spool Ordering:</h3>
            <p>The spool list automatically organizes your spools in priority order:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>▶ "Next to use"</strong> indicator shows which spool should be used first</li>
                <li><strong>Partially-used spools</strong> appear at the top (finish opened spools before starting new
                    ones)
                </li>
                <li><strong>Full spools</strong> ordered by age (oldest first - FIFO inventory management)</li>
                <li><strong>Empty spools</strong> shown at the bottom</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Automatic Updates:</h3>
            <p>The app automatically updates:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>The remaining weight for that spool</li>
                <li>The total remaining weight for the filament</li>
                <li>Status indicators (OK → Low → Critical)</li>
                <li>Progress bars and percentages</li>
                <li>The "Next to use" indicator if the spool is emptied</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Adding More Spools (Restocking):</h3>
            <p>When you buy more of the same filament color:</p>
            <ol>
                <li>Click on the existing filament in your Inventory</li>
                <li>Click the "➕ Add New Spool" button in the detail view</li>
                <li>Enter the new spool's details (weight, type, material)</li>
                <li><strong>Optional:</strong> Enter the purchase price per kg (used for cost calculator)</li>
                <li>The new spool will be added to the same grouped filament</li>
            </ol>

            <p>
                <em>Pro tip: After each print, weigh your spool and calculate the difference,
                    or use your slicer's estimated filament usage. The visual "Next to use" indicator
                    helps you follow FIFO inventory practices automatically!</em>
            </p>
        </div>
        @backToTop
    </div>

    <div class="formCard" id="pricing" style="scroll-margin-top: 20px;">
        <h2 style="margin-top: 0;">💰 Weighted Average Pricing</h2>
        <div style="color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.8;">
            <p>
                The app now features <strong>intelligent weighted average pricing</strong> for accurate cost
                calculations
                that reflect your actual purchase prices over time.
            </p>

            <h3>How It Works:</h3>
            <p>Each spool can have its own purchase price per kilogram:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>When adding new filament:</strong> Enter the "Purchase Price Per Kg" field (optional)</li>
                <li><strong>When adding new spools:</strong> Each spool can have a different purchase price</li>
                <li><strong>In the calculator:</strong> The app uses the weighted average of all spool prices</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Example Scenario:</h3>
            <p>You have PLA Matte Black with 4 spools purchased at different times:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Spool 1: Purchased at 120 DKK/kg</li>
                <li>Spool 2: Purchased at 120 DKK/kg</li>
                <li>Spool 3: Purchased at 180 DKK/kg (premium batch)</li>
                <li>Spool 4: Purchased at 200 DKK/kg (sale price)</li>
            </ul>
            <p><strong>Calculated Average:</strong> (120 + 120 + 180 + 200) / 4 = <strong>155 DKK/kg</strong></p>
            <p>This average is automatically used in the Print Cost Calculator!</p>

            <h3>Adding Prices to Existing Filaments:</h3>
            <ol>
                <li>Click on any filament in Inventory</li>
                <li>Select a spool from the list</li>
                <li>In the "Edit Spool Details" section, find "Purchase Price Per Kg"</li>
                <li>Enter the price and click "Save All Changes"</li>
                <li>The calculated average updates <strong>immediately</strong></li>
            </ol>

            <h3>Price Display:</h3>
            <p>In the filament detail modal, you'll see:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>💰 Calculated Average Price</strong> - The weighted average from all spools</li>
                <li><strong>Source indicator</strong> - Shows how the price is calculated:
                    <ul>
                        <li>"Average from X spool(s) with prices" - Using spool prices</li>
                        <li>"Using manual override price" - If you set a fixed price</li>
                        <li>"Default price" - Fallback if no prices are set (149 DKK/kg)</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li><strong>Manual Price Override</strong> - Option to set a fixed price that ignores spool averages
                </li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Calculator Integration:</h3>
            <p>When using the Print Cost Calculator:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Select filament from your inventory in the material dropdown</li>
                <li>The calculated average price <strong>auto-fills</strong> automatically</li>
                <li>No need to look up prices - always accurate!</li>
                <li>Reflects your actual costs including bulk discounts and price changes</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Benefits:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>✅ <strong>Accurate costing</strong> - Uses real purchase prices</li>
                <li>✅ <strong>Historical tracking</strong> - See what you paid for each batch</li>
                <li>✅ <strong>Automatic averaging</strong> - No manual calculations needed</li>
                <li>✅ <strong>Flexible</strong> - Can override with manual price if needed</li>
                <li>✅ <strong>Backward compatible</strong> - Works without prices (uses default)</li>
            </ul>

            <p>
                <em>💡 Pro tip: When restocking, always enter the purchase price for new spools.
                    Over time, this builds an accurate picture of your true filament costs, making
                    your print cost estimates much more reliable!</em>
            </p>
        </div>
        @backToTop
    </div>

