                <li><strong>Click "Save Currency"</strong> to apply changes</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>⚖️ Stock Thresholds (Customizable!)</h3>
            <p>Configure when filaments should be marked as "Low" or "Critical" based on your needs:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Low Threshold</strong> - Weight (in grams) below which filaments show yellow warning
                    <ul>
                        <li>Default: 500g (typical for one full standard spool)</li>
                        <li>Range: 1g - 10,000g</li>
                        <li>Example: Set to 300g if you print smaller objects</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li><strong>Critical Threshold</strong> - Weight below which filaments show red alert
                    <ul>
                        <li>Default: 250g (about 1/4 of a standard spool)</li>
                        <li>Range: 1g - 10,000g</li>
                        <li>Must be less than Low Threshold</li>
                        <li>Example: Set to 100g if you want earlier warnings</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li><strong>Changes apply immediately</strong> - The inventory view updates in real-time</li>
                <li><strong>Saved to database</strong> - Your preferences persist across app restarts</li>
            </ul>

            <p><em>💡 Tip: If you mainly print large objects, set higher thresholds (e.g., Low: 700g, Critical: 400g).
                    For small prints, lower thresholds work well (e.g., Low: 300g, Critical: 150g).</em></p>

            <h3>Data Import/Export</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Export to CSV</strong> - Download all your filament data as a CSV file for backup or
                    analysis
                    <ul>
                        <li>Includes all filament details and spool information</li>
