                    <ul>
                        <li>Useful for migrating from another system</li>
                        <li>Format should match the export structure</li>
                        <li>Multiple rows with same Brand/Type/Color will be grouped automatically</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ul>

            <h3>🏷️ Brand Management</h3>
            <p>Manage the brands that appear in the dropdown when adding filaments:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>View All Brands</strong> - See all saved brands with their date added</li>
                <li><strong>Delete Brands</strong> - Remove brands you no longer use from the list
                    <ul>
                        <li>Note: Deleting a brand does NOT delete existing filaments with that brand</li>
                        <li>It only removes the brand from the dropdown menu</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li><strong>Add New Brands</strong> - Two ways to add brands:
                    <ul>
                        <li>Use the "➕ Other (Add Custom)" option when adding filaments</li>
                        <li>New brands are automatically saved to the database</li>
                        <li>They instantly appear in the dropdown for future filaments</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li><strong>Popular brands built-in</strong> - The dropdown includes common brands like Bambu Lab,
                    Polymaker, eSUN, and more
                </li>
            </ul>

            <p><em>💡 Tip: Keep your brand list clean by deleting brands you no longer use. This makes the dropdown
                    easier to navigate.</em></p>

            <h3>📡 MQTT & Printer Setup</h3>
            <p>BambuLab connection setup moved to the <strong>MQTT</strong> page. Use it to:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Add/edit printer entries (IP, Access Code, Serial Number, location, default printer)</li>
                <li>Test and connect/disconnect each printer</li>
                <li>Configure MQTT Relay (port, optional username/password)</li>
            </ul>
            <p>See <a href="#multiprinter">MQTT (Printers & Relay)</a> for the full walkthrough.</p>

            <h3>🔄 AMS Auto-Weight Sync</h3>
            <p>When a printer is connected through the <strong>MQTT</strong> page, AMS sync options become available:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <strong>Auto-update spool weight from AMS</strong> — When checked, the app reads the remaining
                    percentage reported by the AMS RFID chip and automatically updates the matching spool's weight in
                    your inventory. The calculation is: <em>AMS% × spool total weight</em>.
                    <ul>
                        <li>Only applies to spools you have <strong>tagged / linked</strong> in the AMS page</li>
                        <li>Non-tagged (third-party) spools are never touched</li>
                        <li>Updates trigger every time the printer sends an AMS message (roughly every 2 s)</li>
                        <li>A change smaller than 0.5 g is ignored to avoid constant DB writes</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Only decrease (never add filament back)</strong> — A sub-option of the above that acts
                    as a safety guard. When checked (the default), the sync will only write a lower weight than what
                    is already in the inventory — it will never increase it.
                    <ul>
                        <li><em>Leave this ON</em> if you trust your manual records and just want the AMS to keep them
                            current as you print
                        </li>
                        <li><em>Turn this OFF</em> if you want full two-way sync — useful if you accidentally
                            over-recorded usage and want the AMS RFID reading to correct it
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ul>
            <p>See the <a href="#amssync">AMS Auto-Weight Sync section</a> for a detailed walkthrough.</p>

            <h3>📡 MQTT Message Log</h3>
            <p>The built-in diagnostic terminal now lives on the <strong>MQTT</strong> page. It displays the last 50 raw MQTT
                messages in real time. See the <a href="#mqttterminal">MQTT Message Log section</a> for details.</p>

            <h3>Database Management</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Purge Database</strong> - Delete ALL filaments from the database
                    <ul>
                        <li>⚠️ This action cannot be undone!</li>
                        <li>Export your data first if you might need it later</li>
                        <li>Useful for starting fresh or clearing test data</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        @backToTop
    </div>

